line_1: Meanwhile the blust'ring wind the deep deforms,
line_2: And Boreas vext your slave with all his storms.

line_1: Hatred to madness wrought each face deforms,
line_2: Lo, at his call, impetuous as the storms,

line_1: With one stern frown the wide-spread deep deforms,
line_2: And works the madding ocean into storms.

line_1: When winter's hand the rough'ning year deforms,
line_2: And hollow winds foretel approaching storms,

line_1: And one brown hue the sun-burnt plain deforms.
line_2: There half the year descends in watry storms;

line_1: Sweet Peace whose brow no ruffling frown deforms,
line_2: And Courage smiling 'midst a thousand storms.
